This paper focuses on multi-agent reinforcement learning for mobile robot navigation, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and robotics (RO). The paper also discusses the use of policy gradient algorithms, which falls under machine learning (LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of mutual adaptation in non-stationary domains, which relates to systems and control (SY). Finally, the paper proposes a curriculum-based strategy for learning interactive policies, which is a technique commonly used in multi-agent systems (MA).
